<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>All the Mods 10 server</title>
<meta name="description" content="How to install and connect to our All the Mods 10 Minecraft server, written for players and their parents.">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #14161a;
    --panel: #1e2128;
    --panel-2: #262a33;
    --text: #e8eaed;
    --muted: #a7adba;
    --accent: #5db462;
    --accent-2: #7fd884;
    --border: #333844;
    --warn-bg: #3a2c14;
    --warn-border: #7a5a1e;
    --warn-text: #f4d58b;
    --code-bg: #0f1115;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
    :root {
      --bg: #f4f6f8;
      --panel: #ffffff;
      --panel-2: #eef1f5;
      --text: #1b1e24;
      --muted: #566072;
      --accent: #2f8f43;
      --accent-2: #257035;
      --border: #d7dde5;
      --warn-bg: #fff5db;
      --warn-border: #e2b657;
      --warn-text: #6b4e12;
      --code-bg: #eef1f5;
    }
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font: 16px/1.6 system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.1rem 4rem; }
  header { text-align: center; padding: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin: 0.2rem 0; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; margin: 2.4rem 0 0.8rem; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin: 0 0 0.3rem; }
  .tagline { color: var(--muted); margin: 0.2rem 0 0; }
  .card {
    background: var(--panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem;
    margin: 1.2rem 0;
  }
  .connect { text-align: center; }
  .addr {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem;
    background: var(--code-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.7rem 0.95rem; margin: 0.4rem 0;
    font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 600;
  }
  .addr code { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
  .copy {
    font: inherit; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer;
    background: var(--accent); color: #06210b; border: 0;
    border-radius: 7px; padding: 0.35rem 0.6rem;
  }
  .copy:hover { background: var(--accent-2); }
  .fallback { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-top: 0.4rem; }
  .fallback code { background: var(--code-bg); padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem; border-radius: 5px; }
  .badge {
    display: inline-block; background: var(--accent); color: #06210b;
    font-weight: 700; border-radius: 999px; padding: 0.25rem 0.8rem; font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .btns { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.7rem; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .btn {
    display: inline-block; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 9px; padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text); background: var(--panel-2);
  }
  .btn.primary { background: var(--accent); color: #06210b; border-color: transparent; }
  .btn:hover { filter: brightness(1.08); }
  .note {
    background: var(--warn-bg); border: 1px solid var(--warn-border);
    color: var(--warn-text); border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.8rem 1rem; margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  ol.steps { counter-reset: step; list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  ol.steps > li {
    position: relative; background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem 1.1rem 3.4rem; margin: 0.9rem 0;
  }
  ol.steps > li::before {
    counter-increment: step; content: counter(step);
    position: absolute; left: 1rem; top: 1.05rem;
    width: 1.7rem; height: 1.7rem; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent); color: #06210b; font-weight: 700;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  }
  ol.steps p { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
  .shot { margin: 0.8rem 0 0.2rem; }
  .shot img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border); display: block; }
  .shot figcaption { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 0.4rem; }
  ul.rules { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  ul.rules li { margin: 0.35rem 0; }
  code { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }
  .em { color: var(--accent-2); font-weight: 600; }
  footer { text-align: center; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  footer a { color: var(--muted); }
  a { color: var(--accent-2); }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

  <header>
    <div class="badge">Now running pack version {{.PackVersion}}</div>
    <h1>All the Mods 10</h1>
    <p class="tagline">A small, whitelist-only Minecraft server for friends and their kids.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="card connect">
    <h3>Connect</h3>
    <div class="addr">
      <code id="addr">{{.ServerAddress}}</code>
      <button class="copy" data-copy="{{.ServerAddress}}" type="button">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <p class="fallback">If your launcher will not connect, use the explicit address <code>{{.FallbackAddress}}</code> instead.</p>
    <div class="btns">
      <a class="btn primary" href="{{.MapPath}}">Open the live map</a>
      <a class="btn" href="#setup">How do I get on?</a>
    </div>
    <p class="fallback">The server is whitelist only. You have to be added before you can join; ask Dan.</p>
  </section>

  <h2 id="setup">Setting up: a guide for players and parents</h2>
  <p>This takes about fifteen minutes. The single most common problem is running the
  <span class="em">wrong version</span> of the modpack, so please read step 3 carefully. If a
  connection fails with a confusing message about mods, the answer is almost always
  "match the server's version," never a setting to change.</p>

  <ol class="steps">

    <li>
      <h3>Install Minecraft: Java Edition</h3>
      <p>Buy and install <span class="em">Minecraft: Java Edition</span> using a Microsoft account.
      Bedrock Edition (the version on consoles, phones, and the Windows Store) is a different game
      and cannot join this server.</p>
      <p>During setup you pick a <span class="em">Java profile name</span>. That name, not your Xbox
      gamertag, is what gets added to the whitelist. Write it down exactly (capital letters and
      underscores matter) and send it to Dan.</p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <h3>Install the CurseForge app</h3>
      <p>Download and install the free <span class="em">CurseForge</span> app. It manages modpacks
      and keeps them separate from your normal Minecraft.</p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <h3>Install All the Mods 10, version {{.PackVersion}}</h3>
      <p>In CurseForge, search for <span class="em">All the Mods 10</span> and open it. Do
      <span class="em">not</span> click the big blue Install button: it always installs the newest
      version, which will not match the server and will fail to connect.</p>
      <p>Instead open the <span class="em">Versions</span> tab, find
      <span class="em">All the Mods 10-{{.PackVersion}}</span> in the list, and install that exact one.</p>
      <figure class="shot">
        <img src="/assets/atm10-7-1.png"
             alt="The CurseForge app on the All the Mods 10 Versions tab, installing version {{.PackVersion}} from the version list rather than the default Install button.">
        <figcaption>The Versions tab. Install version {{.PackVersion}} from this list, not the default Install button.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="note">Later, CurseForge will offer to update the pack. Do not accept those updates
      until the server announces a version change. Everyone has to move at the same time, or the
      updated players can no longer connect.</div>
    </li>

    <li>
      <h3>Give it enough memory</h3>
      <p>Modpacks need a lot of memory. In CurseForge settings, raise the allocated memory to about
      <span class="em">8 GB</span> on a computer with 16 GB of RAM, or about <span class="em">5 GB</span>
      on a computer with 8 GB. Too little memory is the usual cause of freezes and crashes.</p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <h3>Add the server and join</h3>
      <p>Launch All the Mods 10 from CurseForge. On the Minecraft title screen choose
      <span class="em">Multiplayer</span>, then <span class="em">Add Server</span>, and enter the
      address:</p>
      <p><code>{{.ServerAddress}}</code></p>
      <p>If your launcher refuses to connect, edit the server and use <code>{{.FallbackAddress}}</code> instead.</p>
      <p>Make sure Dan has already added your Java profile name to the whitelist; until then the
      server will turn you away.</p>
    </li>

  </ol>

  <h2>House rules</h2>
  <section class="card">
    <ul class="rules">
      <li>Be kind. This is a small server for friends; treat people the way you want to be treated.</li>
      <li>No griefing or stealing. Do not break, take, or change other people's builds and chests.
      The server keeps a log of who changed which blocks, so this is easy to check.</li>
      <li>Ask before building right next to someone or borrowing their things.</li>
      <li>No cheats or hacked clients. Play the pack as it comes.</li>
      <li>Run pack version {{.PackVersion}}, the same as everyone else, and only update when the
      server says to.</li>
      <li>Have fun and build something cool.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>Inviting a friend? <a href="{{.InvitePath}}">Sign in to the invite page</a>.</p>
    <p>&copy; {{.Year}} &middot; a homelab All the Mods 10 server</p>
  </footer>

</div>

<script>
  // Progressive enhancement: copy-to-clipboard. If the API is missing or the
  // page is served without JS, the address is still plainly visible above.
  document.querySelectorAll(".copy").forEach(function (b) {
    b.addEventListener("click", function () {
      var text = b.getAttribute("data-copy");
      if (!navigator.clipboard) return;
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function () {
        var old = b.textContent;
        b.textContent = "Copied";
        setTimeout(function () { b.textContent = old; }, 1200);
      });
    });
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
